Hello! I have a module that has text on one side and an image on the other. I am trying to make the image fill the space like my first image below but the code I have is reflected in the second image. Can someone tell me what I have wrong?   &lt;div class="span12 widget-span {{ widget.background }}"&gt;

    &lt;div class="span12 widget-span {{ widget.page_center }} background-text"&gt;

        &lt;div class="standard-z1 generic-padding widget-span"&gt;

            &lt;div class="image-block center-content span5 {{ widget.content_alignment }} "&gt;

                &lt;img src="{{ widget.featured_image.src }}" width="{{ widget.featured_image.width }}" height="auto" alt="{{ widget.featured_image.alt }}"&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;!-- End Image --&gt;
            &lt;div class="span7 text {{ widget.content_alignment }} {{ widget.tight_text_or_wide_text }} {{ widget.text_closer_to_image_or_farther_away }}"&gt;
                {{ widget.content_block_text }}
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;!-- End Text --&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;!-- End Module Layout --&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;!-- End Page Center --&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;!-- End Background --&gt;

&lt;style&gt;

.image-block {
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
}

&lt;/style&gt;
